-- BAIC Motor May Seek Initial Public Offering in Two Years, China Daily Says
-- B y   M a r k   L e e
-- 2010-10-10T23:54:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/baic-motor-may-seek-initial-public-offering-in-two-years-china-daily-says.html
 BAIC Motor Co., a unit of Beijing
Automotive Industry Holding Co., may sell shares in an initial
public offering in about two years, China Daily reported today,
citing unidentified people at the parent. There are no details
of where the company may seek the listing, according to the
English-language newspaper. Beijing Automotive has partnerships
with Daimler AG and Hyundai Motor, according to China Daily.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Lee in Hong Kong at 
